description: The Company Dataset API allows users to retrieve specific datasets related to companies, such as job listings, decision makers, news articles, G2 etc.

auth_token.description: API key or auth token required for authentication.
note: You need to provide `$auth_token`: Your Crustdata API Key/Auth Token.
Reach out to support@crustdata.com through your company email if not available.

company_id: the unique identifier of a company in our database. It is unique and it never changes. It is numeric.

job_listing.description: Use this request to get job listings that were last updated by the company on 1st Feb, 2024 for all companies with given company_id(s)

filters.description: An object containing the filter conditions.

op.description: The operator to apply on the conditions.

condition.description: An array of complex filter objects or basic filter objects.

column.description: The name of the column to filter.

type.description: The filter type. The value can be =>, =<, =, !=, in, (.), [.]

in.description: Exactly matches atleast one of the elements of list

allow_null.description: A Boolean flag. Whether to allow null values. The value can be true or false.

offset.description: The starting point of the result set. Default value is 0.
offset.note: To retrieve all the jobs listings, keep iterating over offset field in the payload.

limit.description: The number of results to return in a single request.
limit.note: Do not increase limit beyond 100 as the result will be truncated without any ordering.

aggregations.description: List of column objects you want to aggregate on with a condition.

functions.description: List of functions you want to apply.

groups.description: List of groups by which you want to apply.

background_task.description: A boolean flag. If true, triggers a background task to update jobs for up to 10 companies at a time.
background_task.return_value: Returns a task ID that can be used to fetch results later
notes: Updates job listings for up to **10 companies** at a time in the background.
Returns a task ID in the response. Use this task ID to check the status or results via the endpoint `task/result/<task_id>`.

sync_from_source.description: A boolean flag. If true, fetches up to 100 jobs in real-time. Requires a filter on company_id and only allows one company_id in the filter.
notes: Allows fetching up to 100 jobs in real-time (*use `background_task` if all the jobs need to be fetched*).

job_listing.response: The response format is same as that of Company Discovery: Screening API.

investor_portfolio.description: Retrieve portfolio details for a specified investor. Each investor, as returned in the company enrichment endpoint, has a unique identifier (UUID), name, and type. This API allows you to fetch the full portfolio of companies associated with an investor, using either the investor's uuid or name as an identifier.
investor_portfolio.note: uuid for an investor can be retrieved from /screener/company response. It is available in funding_and_investment.crunchbase_investors_info_list[*].uuid

  --header 'Accept-Language: en-US,en;q=0.9' \
  --header 'Authorization: Token $auth_token'
